description.narrative: DNDi is running the world’s first and only randomized comparative clinical trial for mycetoma, working with its partners on a safe, effective, and affordable treatment. Following advocacy from DNDi and its partners, WHO added mycetoma to the list of NTDs in 2016 – an important step in raising awareness of the disease and encouraging investment in research for diagnostics and treatments that can be easily used in rural areas.
Study the efficacy of fosravuconazole to develop a new treatment for mycetoma that can prevent devastating amputation and disability – and to ensure access for all people in need.
